      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH, and relative hemolysis index, RH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint. Required level 2 mandates documented traceability from simulation output to device performance specification.",
      "rationale": "NIH and RH are established hemolysis metrics per ASTM F1841. Traceability documented from CFD shear stress output through power-law hemolysis model to NIH. RH < 1 acceptance criterion directly maps to predicate device comparison requirement."
    },
