      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model inputs (fluid properties, geometry tolerances, boundary condition values) must be traceable to measured or published reference values with documented uncertainty. Required level 2 mandates input uncertainty quantification for primary QoI-sensitive parameters.",
      "rationale": "Blood analog fluid properties (viscosity, density) sourced from published literature with uncertainty bounds. Pump geometry digitized from FDA benchmark CAD files. Inlet velocity profiles derived from experimental flow measurements. Sensitivity analysis confirms hemolysis index most sensitive to rotational speed (±0.5%) and inlet flow rate (±1.2%)."
